The paper deals with the development of a new transform for image and video coding, specifically for depth images. It utilizes graph signal processing and constructs a one-state Markov process to model inter-pixel correlations and anti-correlations. The paper also discusses the importance of self-loops in the graph to ensure positive semi-definiteness. Based on this information, the most likely sub-categories are cs.IT (information theory), cs.CV (computer vision), and cs.MM (multimedia). The paper also involves experimental results, which suggest that it could belong to cs.SI (signal processing) or cs.LG (machine learning).
